hoffa a detroit labor lawyer said wednesday the jackets are 
a reaffirmation of the feelings towards the hoffa contribution to 
the union he refused to say if he would be a candidate when the 
16millionmember union holds its elections in june 1991 
the elections are part of a 1989 settlement of a lawsuit in 
which the federal government linked dozens of teamsters executives 
to a pattern of racketeering including 20 murders 
jimmy hoffa disappeared in 1975 after being released from 
federal prison where he was serving a sentence for mail fraud an 
jury tampering he is presumed to have been killed by the mob 
