more than 50000 pieces of mail have flooded 
into jeanne whites home since her son ryan died from aids 
we still havent even gotten the mail open yet mrs white 
said wednesday shaking her head although phil donahue and his 
wife marlo thomas hired a secretary to help mrs white to sort 
through the letters 
she and the secretary shelley henson are still opening 
getwell letters that arrived at riley hospital for children in 
indianapolis before white died of complications from acquired 
immune deficiency syndrome on april 8 
white 18 became a wellknown spokesman for aids education 
after fighting a lengthy court battle to attend public school 
its surprising everybody is still calling mrs white said 
i cant believe how many kids he touched 
now the favor is being returned from people all over the world 
she digs through the piles of mail to read favorite pieces out loud 
to henson and displays the large banners sent from school children 
from across the country 
its a healing process she said but henson finds it difficult 
i know i probably cry an average of four times a day she 
said 
mrs white has been on leave of absence since last fall when 
ryan began suffering more frequent bouts of illness she said she 
is considering early retirement to further her sons work in aids 
education 
im not sure what im going to do said mrs white who is 
being helped financially by celebrity friends whom she declined to 
indentify 
about 35000 has been donated to four funds set up in her sons 
name mrs white said 
the ryan white memorial fund was established to help mrs white 
