that issue because that is one of the foremost issues right now 
that separate the alliance from the position of the soviet union 
baker said 
the united states and west germany have offered a solution a 
united germany would belong to nato but soviet troops would remain 
temporarily on east german soil while nato troops keep out of that 
territory 
moscow has rejected that idea suggesting a compromise that the 
west rebuffed making a united germany a member of both the 
sovietled warsaw pact and nato until alternative security 
structures can be set up within europe 
western diplomats worry the soviets will try to widen the agenda 
of the twoplusfour talks to include disarmament matters and to 
embrace moscows hopes of setting up brandnew security structures 
within europe 
broadening the agenda could slow the unification process 
both west germany and the united states have tried to allay 
soviet worries about unification 
washington said thursday it had scrapped plans to modernize 
shortrange nuclear missiles based in west germany 
west germany has said the soviet unions security interests will 
be guaranteed it seems to be offering the soviets economic 
incentives to make up for the loss of east germany as their biggest 
trading partner 
conference participants hope to defuse widespread concerns in 
europe that a stronger germany could again pose a threat to 
countries overrun during the two world wars 
the six nations have already agreed to invite poland to the 
talks when its western border is discussed 
west german chancellor helmut kohl earlier this year caused a 
furor by refusing to guarantee a united germany would not try to 
reclaim land ceded to poland after world war ii 
kohl has since reversed himself but poland will still be taking 
part in the talks at some point to press home its concerns 
after both world wars germany was at the center of 
international talks that helped shape the future of europe 
in july 1945 the leaders of the united states britain and the 
soviet union met in potsdam now in east germany and carved up 
vanquished germany 
in january 1919 27 nations gathered in paris to try to make 
sure germany would never again threaten europe after the carnage of 
world war i 
the result was the treaty of versailles which exacted huge 
reparations from germany and aggravated german bitterness that 
helped adolf hitler rise to power 
the west germans want speedy results from the new talks 
especially now that the two germanys have agreed to merge their two 
economies by july 2 they say they would to finish the talks by 
fall to make way for allgerman elections and full unification next 
year 
</TEXT>
