judge charles p mirarchi jr mirarchi said sprague required a 
preponderance of evidence to prove statements defamed him and 
had to meet the tougher standard of clear and convincing 
evidence to prove falsity actual malice and damages 
sprague sued over articles that he said implied he was involved 
in an illegal wiretapping incident an allegation he denied and 
questioned his role in a homicide case involving a son of a friend 
former state police commissioner rocco urella 
