<TEXT>
china today marked the 71st anniversary of its 
first democracy movement criticizing last mays proreform rallies 
and appealing to young people to devote themselves to communism 
the communist youth league and other official groups organized 
functions to commemorate the may 4th movement but there were 
no reports of unauthorized student activities 
last year on the 70th anniversary of the movement about 
100000 students and supporters surged into tiananmen square for a 
peaceful rally seeking greater freedom an end to official 
corruption and a free press 
the demonstration was one of the high points of the sevenweek 
democracy movement that ended on june 4 when the military stormed 
beijing and seized tiananmen from the students who had occupied it 
the government has since suppressed any further student unrest 
through a harsh campaign of ideological education and intimidation 
the partys official peoples daily in a frontpage editorial 
today said the message to be learned from the may 4th movement 
is that the spirit of patriotism is to be devoted to the cause of 
socialism and the socialist modernization of the motherland 
in an indirect reference to last years student demands for 
rapid democratic reform it noted that in a greenhouse you 
cannot grow trees which reach to the sky 
communist party chief jiang zemin in a speech to about 3000 
invited youths thursday also stressed that last years student 
movement was different from that of may 4 1919 
in 1919 several thousand college students gathered at tiananmen 
gate to demand democracy and modernization their protest sparked 
an intellectual movement that included the creation and expansion 
of the communist party 
jiang said the 1919 campaign was a great antiimperialism and 
antifeudalism movement whereas student activists in 1989 bound 
themselves with foreign hostile forces and conducted activities 
harmful to the motherland 
officially organized events today included the start of a youth 
festival and communist youth leaguesponsored entertainment at a 
park adjacent to the forbidden city 
invited youths watched fashion shows hair styling singing and 
band performances there were booths selling clothing and food and 
a hall for dancing 
tiananmen square was open to the public but large numbers of 
police patrolled the square and its environs 
what became known as the may 4th movement began as a protest of 
the versailles treaty that ended world war i chinas warlord 
government agreed to treaty clauses that endorsed japans seizure 
of parts of china during the war 
although the treaty was the immediate spark that caused the 
protest the main slogans of the students were democracy and 
science by which they meant modernization the government now is 
choosing to eliminate the democracy angle and stress the 
antiimperialism and science aspects of the movement 
</TEXT>
