east germans on sunday will vote in local 
elections that likely will remove vestiges of communist control and 
virtually complete the revolution that began a year ago 
the balloting will turn over to local hands the obedient 
bureaucracies that were carefully controlled by the former 
stalinist leadership 
now must the selfreliance of the communities be realized 
said wolfgang berghofer the mayor of dresden and a former 
communist who is seeking to retain his post 
the balloting also may provide a gauge of the current mood 
toward german unification a process that is speeding toward 
completion 
there have been widespread protests in recent weeks by workers 
afraid that their factories will close when forced to compete with 
western commerce 
experts met in east berlin on friday to continue talks on 
merging the economies of the german states and the superpowers 
prepared for talks saturday in the west german capital on the 
international implications of a united germany 
