doubledigit figures next month 
government officials hinted that the new tax known as the poll 
tax will still be amended although not changed in principle 
the tax has caused a national furor it is widely perceived as 
unfair because local councils divide the charges for local services 
equally among all adults regardless of income 
it replaced the previous property tax system under which only 
17 million homeowners paid for local services such as education 
police and garbage collection all 38 million adults are liable 
for the new tax with rebates for the 95 million poorest 
mrs thatcher introduced the new system thinking that it would 
prove to voters that local councils dominated by labor were bigger 
