a 12year odyssey is coming to an end for the 
oldest known drifting iceberg which is beginning to break up in 
the south atlantic the government said friday 
the iceberg once twice the area of washington dc was first 
sighted in 1978 
since then it has drifted some 5700 miles almost entirely 
around antarctica according to the joint ice center operated by 
the navy and the national oceanic and atmospheric administration 
the iceberg was last sighted southwest of the falkland islands 
in february according to navy capt tom callaham he said 
satellite studies show that the berg is now breaking up in a region 
known as the screaming fifties 
that portion of ocean near 50 degrees south latitude is famed 
for its rough weather and powerful winds 
