average of 175000 new jobs a month she said a year ago at this 
time the economy had produced a monthly average of 200000 jobs 
while the 1988 average for the first four months was 275000 
ms norwood said the slowdown is not particularly surprising 
after more than seven years of business expansion 
meanwhile the service sector which has been carrying the 
economy added 179000 jobs bolstered by the hiring of temporary 
census workers 
