the left leg a localization of the disease which afflicted the 
elephant man the ailment caused his left tibia or shin bone to 
bend rather than grow straight 
when he was eight months old he suffered a fractured leg 
because of the illness and underwent several unsuccessful 
operations in missouri his right leg was 3 inches longer than his 
left before this most recent treatment began in february 
