could help josh 
they were directed to weiland an expert in microvascular bone 
grafting in this procedure a bone the surrounding tissue and its 
blood supply are transplanted to another part of the body where 
microsurgery reconnects all the blood vessels 
josh was brought to new york in february to begin the first 
phase of treatment the ilazarov procedure to lengthen the leg 
every day for two months mrs ellison turned three dials 
surgically attached to her sons leg to stretch it out 
the device lengthened his leg by one millimeter per day and 
when josh arrived for the surgery on tuesday the legs were almost 
the same length weiland said doctors took a bone from his right 
leg and implanted it where the diseased bone had been 
if everything continues to work out mrs ellison will bring 
josh back to missouri on monday he will spend the next three 
months wearing a splint to support the transplanted bone with 
weiland expecting to see the boy for a checkup this summer 
