<DOCNO> AP900504-0186 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
everyone has heard the story in one form or 
another since everyone has been affected in some way it is the 
story of the variable dollar 
a person bought a house in 1978 for 50000 and now the house 
has a market value of 100000 what an investment the homeowner 
says or you find that a car worth 5000 five years ago still 
sells for 5000 what a car 
youve been duped by the dollar 
in the case of the house divide by two because the 1990 
dollars buying power is only onehalf that of the 1978 dollar the 
house is still a 50000 house in terms of the 1985 dollar the 
car is worth only 4135 or so 
with some degree of inflation always present in the economy it 
is difficult to make yeartoyear comparisons of anything 
denominated in dollars such as paychecks prices profits and 
gross national product 
everyone dupes himself to some extent uncle sam for instance 
has thrown little celebrations every time the gross national 
product reaches another trillion dollar level knowing full well 
that he isnt dealing with reality 
in reality the buying power of the dollar changes every day 
every week every month every year and almost always downward 
but perceptions are slower to change perhaps there is even a 
slight reluctance to change 
while the changes often are small yeartoyear they add up 
substantially after several years have passed ten years ago for 
instance the 1980 dollar bought 158 worth of goods or services 
as measured by the 1990 dollar 
to determine where you stand financially in 1980 dollars you 
must multiply your current dollar amount by 158 by doing so you 
will find how many 1990 dollars and cents are needed to equal the 
buying power of one 1980 dollar 
if you earned 25000 in 1980 for example you would have to 
earn 25000 times 158 in 1990 or 39500 just to avoid losing 
ground deflating isnt it yes and worse it can be terribly 
misleading and confusing 
in geography for example teachers often lament that if 
students cannot point to the place on the map where they live they 
cant possibly relate to the rest of the world and its peoples 
in economics the lament is only slightly different how can 
individuals relate to the economic world and their progress in it 
if they cant comprehend that the measuring stick changes every 
year 
would it make sense to measure snowfalls by a 12inch stick one 
year and a 9inch stick another or change the value of the quart 
or pound or time races by a 58second minute or change the 
gradations on a thermometer 
with such thoughts in mind martin lefkowitz an economist for 
the national chamber of commerce foundation annually updates an 
index for calculating the impact of inflation all the way back to 
1965 
its a shocker the index for 1965 is 413 meaning you would 
have to have 413 in 1990 dollars to equal the buying power of 
just one 1965 dollar the index for 1970 isnt much better at 336 
here are others at fiveyear intervals from 1990 which is 100 
1985 index 121 1980 158 1975 242 multiply 1990 dollars 
against the index to determine how many 1990 dollars equal 1 in 
those years 
it can be a deflating experience but isnt it better to face 
reality than to live in fantasy 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP900504-0187 </DOCNO>
