<TEXT>
apparel retailers got a lift during april as the arrival of 
easter and spring weather brought consumers back into the stores 
many stores that had a disappointing march fared better last 
month according to figures released thursday by several of the 
nations biggest retailers 
woolworth corp whose sales had fallen in march compared with a 
year earlier had an 182 percent sales gain in april at stores 
open at least a year and a 211 percent increase overall 
results from stores open a year or longer known as same or 
comparablestore sales give a more accurate reading of a 
retailers performance 
sears roebuck and co the nations largest retailer reported 
a 31 percent samestore sales increase and 16 percent overall 
gain 
most of sears improvement was due to clothing sales not the 
companys wellknown line of appliances and other durable goods 
said monroe greenstein a retail industry analyst with bear stearns 
amp co 
consumers still burdened by high installment debt were again 
cautious about major expenditures but they were willing to pick up 
new clothes greenstein said this trend which has been in place 
for several years would continue until later in 1990 
retail sales are closely watched not only as a gauge of the 
industrys health and that of individual companies but also as an 
economic barometer consumer spending accounts for about twothirds 
of the gross national product 
changes in the calendar such as easter falling on april 9 this 
year and on march 26 last year often have an impact on retail 
sales and affect yeartoyear comparisons by inflating results in 
some months 
however after accounting for the shift the industrys results 
in april were generally favorable said jeffrey feiner a retail 
analyst with merrill lynch amp co 
analysts consider march and april sales together in assessing 
how well a store has performed 
among other retailers announcing april results thursday 
walmart stores inc reported a 7 percent increase in 
samestore sales while overall results were up 20 percent 
jc penney co inc had a disappointing month after a much 
stronger march penneys samestore sales fell 28 percent while 
overall sales were off 17 percent 
greenstein said penneys sales looked bleaker than they actually 
were because they were compared against especially strong results 
in april 1989 when the company ran special sales promotions 
