kuwait has caused a worldwide oil glut just as demand traditionally 
eases in the second quarter analysts say 
since about midmarch the price of west texas intermediate 
crude oil has seesawed above 20 a barrel back down to nearly 16 
up again to almost 1950 and then back down again to 18 
the june contract for wti the benchmark grade of us crude 
fell 69 cents thursday to settle at 1799 a barrel on the new york 
mercantile exchange 
