capital requirements and other measures would inevitably entail 
the disappearance of a certain number of stock houses 
in addition to setting minimum capital requirements for brokers 
the reforms will open the exchange to banks and other financial 
institutions tighten rules on insider trading and give more power 
to the belgian banking commission the stock exchange watchdog 
