<TEXT>
federated department stores inc and sister 
allied stores corp posted net losses totaling more than 21 
billion in their fourth fiscal quarters largely because of a 
writedown stemming from their bankruptcy reorganization 
the companies which own nearly 260 us department stores such 
as bloomingdales richs and lazarus also reported that excluding 
nonoperating charges they posted operating profits for both the 
fourth quarter and full fiscal year ended feb 3 
i believe we have turned the corner on stabilizing the 
business and that we are well into a period of operational 
recovery chairman allen questrom said in a prepared statement 
separately the companies parent campeau corp said it had 
proposed a business plan to its bondholders that includes the sale 
of real estate assets and a temporary halt in its interest payments 
federated and allied sought federal bankruptcy court protection 
from creditors on jan 15 citing the burden of paying off 77 
billion in debt much of the debt was incurred when campeau 
acquired the companies federated in 1988 and allied in 1986 
largely with borrowed funds 
worsening the companies condition was a sluggish retailing 
environment which forced pricecutting and other competitive moves 
that cut into profits 
federated said it lost 134 billion during the fourth quarter 
on sales of 159 billion compared with a profit of 276 million 
and sales of 149 billion in the yearearlier quarter 
the results were sharply affected by a 115 billion writedown 
of goodwill the amount over federateds book value that campeau 
paid to acquire the company in 1988 an accounting move made to 
reflect the deterioration of federateds financial situation during 
the year 
federateds earnings also were reduced by 1265 million in 
deferred financing and reorganization costs and by 5161 million 
in net interest expense 
the company had operating income of 486 million down from 
1759 million a year earlier 
allied said it lost 8368 million on sales of 8922 million 
compared with a profit of 376 million on sales of 8698 million a 
year earlier 
allieds earnings were reduced by nonoperating charges of 
6603 million for its equity in federated 2906 million in net 
interest expense and 1388 million in income tax expense 
the companys operating income was 252 million in the quarter 
down from 862 million a year earlier 
for the full year federated posted a net loss of 15 billion 
compared with a loss of 1563 billion a year earlier sales rose 
72 percent to 487 billion from 357 billion 
allieds net loss on the year was 9252 million compared with 
a profit of 514 million the previous year sales rose 52 percent 
to 27 billion from 257 billion 
at the end of the fiscal year federated had 367 million in 
cash on hand and allied had 185 million in cash the companies 
reported 
both also showed positive cash flows 3724 million for 
federated and 1997 million for allied for the full year although 
the companies are not making interest payments while in bankruptcy 
court reorganization 
federated owns the bloomingdales lazarus abraham and straus 
richs and burdines chains allieds chains include jordan marsh 
sterns maas brothers and the bon marche 
campeau which spun off its department store businesses shortly 
before they entered bankruptcy court protection is attempting to 
work out of its own financial problems 
in a business plan proposed to holders of 184 million of its 
debentures campeau said it would ask bondholders to waive any 
defaults and defer interest payments through dec 31 1991 
in return the company would sell assets from its real estate 
holdings to make a major reduction in its secured debt campeau 
also would pay secured loans with cash flow from the properties 
used as collateral 
bondholders would consider the plan at a previously scheduled 
june 1 meeting in toronto 
campeaus real estate holdings consist primarily of shopping 
malls and office complexes and business in the united states and 
canada 
</TEXT>
